#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/interest_calculator.html:245
msgid "Set Rate & Time"
msgstr "Definir taxa e tempo"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/interest_calculator.html:246
msgid "Enter the annual interest rate and time period."
msgstr "Insira a taxa de juros anual e o período de tempo."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/interest_calculator.html:252
msgid "Choose Type"
msgstr "Escolha o tipo"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/interest_calculator.html:253
msgid "Select simple or compound interest."
msgstr "Selecione juros simples ou compostos."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/interest_calculator.html:265
msgid "What's the difference between simple and compound interest?"
msgstr "Qual é a diferença entre juros simples e compostos?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/interest_calculator.html:271
msgid ""
"Simple interest is calculated only on the principal. Compound interest is "
"calculated on the principal plus accumulated interest. Compound interest "
"grows faster because you earn 'interest on interest'."
msgstr ""
"Os juros simples são calculados apenas sobre o principal. Os juros compostos"
" são calculados sobre o principal mais os juros acumulados. Os juros "
"compostos crescem mais rápido porque você ganha “juros sobre juros”."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/interest_calculator.html:277
msgid "What is effective interest rate?"
msgstr "O que é taxa de juros efetiva?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/interest_calculator.html:283
msgid ""
"The effective rate is the actual annual return when compounding is factored "
"in. For simple interest, it equals the stated rate. For compound interest, "
"it's higher due to compounding effects."
msgstr ""
"A taxa efetiva é o retorno anual real quando a capitalização é "
"contabilizada. Para juros simples, é igual à taxa declarada. Para juros "
"compostos, é maior devido aos efeitos compostos."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/interest_calculator.html:289
msgid "How does compounding frequency matter?"
msgstr "Como a frequência composta é importante?"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/interest_calculator.html:295
msgid ""
"More frequent compounding means more interest. Daily compounding earns "
"slightly more than monthly, which earns more than annually. However, the "
"difference becomes smaller at higher frequencies."
msgstr ""
"Composições mais frequentes significam mais juros. A composição diária rende"
" um pouco mais do que a mensal, que rende mais do que anualmente. No "
"entanto, a diferença torna-se menor em frequências mais altas."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/interest_calculator.html:303
msgid "Interest Tips"
msgstr "Dicas de interesse"

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/interest_calculator.html:309
msgid ""
"For savings, look for accounts with daily compounding to maximize returns."
msgstr ""
"Para economizar, procure contas com capitalização diária para maximizar os "
"retornos."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/interest_calculator.html:315
msgid ""
"The Rule of 72: Divide 72 by your interest rate to estimate years to double."
msgstr ""
"A Regra dos 72: Divida 72 pela sua taxa de juros para estimar que os anos "
"dobrarão."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/interest_calculator.html:321
msgid ""
"Start saving early - time is the most powerful factor in compound growth."
msgstr ""
"Comece a economizar cedo – o tempo é o fator mais poderoso no crescimento "
"composto."

#: Financial_Calculators/templates/financial_calculators/interest_calculator.html:327
msgid "For loans, prefer simple interest to pay less over time."
msgstr ""
"Para empréstimos, prefira juros simples para pagar menos ao longo do tempo."

